<span class="sectionhdr">Team Formation & Player Eligibility</span><br>				
Boys and girls in grades 9-12 starting 2010-11 school year attending a High School within the Beaverton School District, and within the boundaries of the Tualatin Hills Park & Recreation District (THPRD).<br>
<br>
Non-Beaverton School District students (private and home schooled) are eligible if the school location or residence is within the THPRD boundaries.  Players need to provide school ID showing that they are enrolled in school and need to pay the Out of District assessment fee if they reside outside the THPRD boundaries.<br>
<br>
Players can form their own teams of students from a School District 48 High School or a private school within the THPRD boundaries.  <strong>Teams must carry a minimum of 8 players and may carry a maximum or 14 players on their roster. Each team is also required to secure their adult coach that is 21 years or older.</strong><br>
<br>
<strong>Note:</strong> Junior, Sophmore and Freshmen players who played on their winter high school basketball teams(Varsity, JV I, JV II, Sophemore or Freshmen) are eligible to play in the THPRD summer recreational basketball program.<br>
<br>
